A similar procedure is followed for the other capacitors. Specifically, $\mathrm{DV}_{\mathrm{xi}}$ is determined by connecting all capacitors smaller than $\mathrm{C}_{i}$ to $\mathrm{V}_{\text {ref }}$, connecting $\mathrm{C}_{i}$ and all larger capacitors to ground while the comparator is reset, then taking the comparator out of reset mode, switching all smaller capacitors to ground, $\mathrm{C}_{i}$ to $\mathrm{V}_{\text {ref }}$, and leaving all larger capacitors grounded. $\mathrm{DV}_{\mathrm{xi}}$ is then found using the cal-dac and successive approximation. $\mathrm{DV}_{\mathrm{ei}}$ is finally calculated using the formula

$$
\begin{equation*}
